{
  "text": "Of note is the absence of sqt/ndr1 from our list, as it was previously shown to be an early essential component of the dorsal induction pathway [CITATION_1] . This finding is most likely explained by the maternal component of ndr1, also observed in ich embryos [CITATION_2] , wich will buffer the changes occurring during MBT at the dorsal side. The activation of the Fgf-signaling pathway, itself dependent on Nodal-signaling [CITATION_3] is also indicative that the dorsal activation of ndr1 in fact occurs.",
